was reduced for the preschoolers
to a five-point gap.

00:29:14.085 --> 00:29:18.156
It's so compelling you cannot
avoid having the conversation:

00:29:18.156 --> 00:29:19.783
"Why not invest early?"

00:29:26.431 --> 00:29:28.032
Narrator:
High quality child-care

00:29:28.032 --> 00:29:30.558
and preschool is just one
of the solution.

00:29:32.370 --> 00:29:33.772
Polk:
Early childcare education

00:29:33.772 --> 00:29:35.540
is not a panacea.

00:29:35.540 --> 00:29:38.576
You have to have clean,
safe neighborhoods, good food,

00:29:38.576 --> 00:29:43.207
good communities, you have
a support system around us all.

00:29:45.717 --> 00:29:47.085
Narrator:
Economists are clear

00:29:47.085 --> 00:29:48.887
about the equation:

00:29:48.887 --> 00:29:51.055
our system is paying
for failure,

00:29:51.055 --> 00:29:53.251
rather than
investing in success.

00:29:54.058 --> 00:29:56.094
Not just one study, there
are actually four

00:29:56.094 --> 00:29:58.396
independent longitudinal
studies on early ed,

00:29:58.396 --> 00:30:02.060
all getting very, very high
annual rates of return.

00:30:03.401 --> 00:30:04.969
Narrator:
The question is,

00:30:04.969 --> 00:30:07.472
What will we do about it?

00:30:07.472 --> 00:30:11.609
How much are we willing
to invest for the long term?

00:30:11.609 --> 00:32:46.664
When are we going to get crazy
about our kids?